<p class="">I am much obliged to the Attorney-General, because that is what I thought he would say. Other people, I am sure, would seek to argue that there was some form of "express malice" in that case because of the felonious enterprise in which they were engaged, but, if not, it is surely a great weakness of the proposed Clause that persons found guilty of murder in such circumstances should escape the death penalty.<p></p> Let me pass to another point. I am making a layman's approach to this and want to be clear, if possible, on the meaning of this very elaborate Clause.</p>                    <div class="hidden-md hidden-lg" style="padding-left: 0px;">
                        <a href="#contribution-109f109b-0304-4aca-b216-c90fa1a74af7" rel="popover" class="link-to-contribution link-to-contribution-mobile link-text" title="Share this contribution" data-placement="top"
