<p class="">Will the Home Secretary allow me to intervene. I apologise for interrupting him, but I think there is a real point here. At the time the Government new Clause is put, assuming that the House has previously carried the Government Motion to disagree with the Lords, the state of this Bill will be that the death penalty will be suspended for five years. On that argument every vote against the Government's new Clause is a vote for the suspension of the death penalty for five years.</p>                    <div class="hidden-md hidden-lg" style="padding-left: 0px;">
